Comet Halley orbits the sun every 75 yea.content:
Taking the insights from the other agents into account, we know that Bill's dad saw the Comet Halley when he was 30, which means x = 30. Bill saw the comet a second time when he was three times the age his father was when he saw the Comet, which gives us the equation B = 3(30 + 75) = 3(105) = 315.

Therefore, Bill was 315 years old when he saw the Comet for the first time.

